    <item>
      <title>Solving Screen Recording Issues on Windows 10</title>
      <link>https://peoplealsoask.github.io/windows-10-screen-recording-issues/</link>
      <pubDate>Thu, 04 Jun 2026 09:16:52 &#43;0700</pubDate>
      <guid>https://peoplealsoask.github.io/windows-10-screen-recording-issues/</guid>
      <description>If you&amp;rsquo;re unable to record your screen on Windows 10, it may be due to a variety of reasons including outdated graphics drivers, disabled screen recording features, or conflicting software. Updating your system, enabling the Game Bar, or using alternative screen recording tools can resolve the issue.</description>
    </item>
    <item>
      <title>Screen Recording in Windows 10 Made Easy</title>
      <link>https://peoplealsoask.github.io/how-to-record-screen-in-windows-10/</link>
      <pubDate>Sun, 24 May 2026 09:16:52 &#43;0700</pubDate>
      <guid>https://peoplealsoask.github.io/how-to-record-screen-in-windows-10/</guid>
      <description>To record your screen in Windows 10, use the Xbox Game Bar or the built-in Screen Recording tool. For more advanced features, consider third-party software like OBS Studio or Camtasia.</description>
    </item>
    <item>
      <title>Screen Recording on Windows 10 with Sound: A Step-by-Step Guide</title>
      <link>https://peoplealsoask.github.io/screen-recording-windows-10-with-sound/</link>
      <pubDate>Thu, 14 May 2026 09:16:52 &#43;0700</pubDate>
      <guid>https://peoplealsoask.github.io/screen-recording-windows-10-with-sound/</guid>
      <description>To record your screen on Windows 10 with sound, use the Xbox Game Bar or third-party software like OBS Studio or Camtasia. These tools allow you to capture your screen and audio simultaneously, making it ideal for creating tutorials, demos, or presentations.</description>
